## 🚀 Getting Started

Follow these steps to set up the Virtual Mentor Bridge locally.

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/virtual-mentor-bridge.git
cd virtual-mentor-bridge
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

Using `npm` (or your preferred package manager):

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file at the root of the project and populate it with your respective keys. Reference `.env.example` if available. You will need:
- Clerk API Keys
- Supabase URL & Anon Key
- Groq & OpenAI API keys
- Calendly URLs & tokens
- Railway internal model endpoint

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk_...
```

### 4. Run the Development Server

Execute the development script:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Your app will be running seamlessly at [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

